         <abstract>
            <p>We present a deterministic polynomial-time algorithm that decides whether a power product Π&lt;sup&gt;k&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;i = 1&lt;/sub&gt;γ&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; is a unit in the ring of integers of K, where K is a number field, γ&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; are nonzero elements of K and n&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; are rational integers. The main algorithm is based on the factor refinement method for ideals, which might be of independent interest.</p>
          </abstract>
